<subSubSection id="C32DF8BD9658FFF1FF27135738A0FB3E" pageId="1" pageNumber="1786" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B88AB369658FFF1FF271357385EFBBA" blockId="1.[178,1086,823,1109]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1786">
Description: Length: ca. 
<quantity id="4CCF06D39658FFF1FD8A13583B6DFCA2" box="[543,610,824,845]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="1786" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 mm</quantity>
; length of fore-body: 
<quantity id="4CCF06D39658FFF1FCC213573AA2FCA2" box="[855,941,823,845]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="1786" unit="mm" value="4.1">4.1 mm</quantity>
. Body black, femora and tibiae pitchy black, mouthparts antennae and tarsi dark brown. Fore-body: 
<figureCitation id="130CB7B39658FFF1FF27131239FDFC68" box="[178,242,882,904]" captionStart="Figs 1-2" captionStartId="10.[178,218,1342,1364]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,224,1281]" captionTargetId="figure-83@10.[178,1085,212,1308]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 1-2: Fore-body (fb), aedoeagus in lateral view (al), aedoeagus in ventral view (av), male sternite VII (s7), male sternite VIII (s8) of: 1: P. magna; 2: P. ullrichi Fig. 1: P. magna 1fb 1al 1av 1s7 1s8" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5873558" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5873558/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1786">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
. Head sub-quadrate, slightly transverse (1 x 
<quantity id="4CCF06D39658FFF1FD5313123A15FC68" box="[710,794,882,903]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="1786" unit="mm" value="1.1">1.1 mm</quantity>
), the anterior margin with a single puncture behind antennal tubercles, one anterior and one posterior puncture on inner margin of eyes, 4-5 unequal punctures near postero-lateral angles and a single row of rather large punctures along posterior margin, the disc impunctate. Pronotum scarcely elongate (1.4 x 
<quantity id="4CCF06D39658FFF1FEC1138738A8FC13" box="[340,423,999,1020]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="1" pageNumber="1786" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
), with discal series of 6 punctures and arcuate lateral series of 4 punctures. Elytra a little elongate (1.5 x 
<quantity id="4CCF06D39658FFF1FDCD14643BA4FBF5" box="[600,683,1028,1050]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="1" pageNumber="1786" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
), with 3 series of punctures. Abdomen more sparsely and irregularly punctured than that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C37D0B59658FFF1FD4014423A38FBD8" authorityName="Rougemont" authorityYear="2015" box="[725,823,1058,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudolathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="1786" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magna">
<emphasis id="B94377249658FFF1FD4014423A38FBD8" box="[725,823,1058,1079]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="1786">P. magna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the interstices devoid of microsculpture.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B88AB369658FFF1FF27140438A0FB3E" blockId="1.[178,1085,1124,1234]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1786">
Male: posterior margin of sternite VII very broadly, shallowly, arcuately excised, laterally with a small tuft of bristles; deep narrow emargination of sternite VIII extending to ½ the length of sternite, the margin of emargination finely and sharply bordered; aedoeagus: 
<figureCitation id="130CB7B39658FFF1FEBC14DC386BFB3D" box="[297,356,1212,1234]" captionStart="Figs 1-2" captionStartId="10.[178,218,1342,1364]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,224,1281]" captionTargetId="figure-83@10.[178,1085,212,1308]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 1-2: Fore-body (fb), aedoeagus in lateral view (al), aedoeagus in ventral view (av), male sternite VII (s7), male sternite VIII (s8) of: 1: P. magna; 2: P. ullrichi Fig. 1: P. magna 1fb 1al 1av 1s7 1s8" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5873558" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5873558/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1786">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
al, 2av.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32DF8BD9658FFF1FF2714813840FAA0" pageId="1" pageNumber="1786" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B88AB369658FFF1FF2714813840FAA0" blockId="1.[178,1086,1249,1359]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1786">
This species belongs to the Nigerrima group. It is about the size of 
<taxonomicName id="4C37D0B59658FFF1FC1214823D03FB18" baseAuthorityName="CAMERON" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[903,1036,1250,1271]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudolathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="1786" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigerrima">
<emphasis id="B94377249658FFF1FC1214823D03FB18" box="[903,1036,1250,1271]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="1786">P. nigerrima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs externally by its dark legs, longer elytra with finer punctures of the discal series. It is larger than the black species from New 
<collectingCountry id="F320EBA69658FFF1FDE1157C3BB2FADD" box="[628,701,1308,1330]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="1" pageNumber="1786">Guinea</collectingCountry>
described by Last and redescribed by ASSING (2014).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
